WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.313
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.774 --> 00:09.518
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.179 --> 00:18.347
You know, the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.467 --> 00:27.736
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:29.417 --> 00:30.258
The heroic

00:30.466 --> 00:35.394
in Christianity, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part two.

00:37.337 --> 00:41.203
For if ye love them which love you, what thank have ye?

00:41.243 --> 00:45.149
For sinners also love those that love them.

00:46.351 --> 00:50.958
And if ye do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye?

00:50.998 --> 00:53.922
For sinners also do even the same.

00:53.963 --> 00:58.770
And if ye lend to them of whom ye hope to receive,

00:59.234 --> 01:00.535
What thank have ye?

01:01.636 --> 01:05.820
For sinners also lend to sinners to receive as much again.

01:07.222 --> 01:10.445
Luke's Gospel, chapter 6, verses 32 to 34.

01:11.066 --> 01:27.922
If you are what you profess to be, my brethren, more is expected from you than from any other people beneath the sun, and therefore I shall throw aside all hesitancy in setting before you a supreme standard.

01:28.706 --> 01:33.853
and asking of you what we never can get from sinners, nor from people of the world.

01:34.434 --> 01:46.489
Do you not know that your Lord has said, except your righteousness shall exceed the righteousness of the scribes and Pharisees, ye shall in no case enter the kingdom of heaven?

01:47.671 --> 01:56.082
If I were called to address an ordinary company of men and women upon feats of valor, I might speak with baited breath.

01:56.354 --> 01:59.137
if I exhorted them to heroism in war.

02:00.499 --> 02:16.759
But if I had lived some thousands of years ago and had been called upon to talk to Spartan warriors, all equipped for battle, men graved and scored with the scars of conflict, I should set no bounds to my exhortations.

02:17.400 --> 02:23.267
I would bestow them as a lion arouses the young lions and urges them to the prey.

02:24.409 --> 02:25.330
I should tell them

02:25.442 --> 02:36.134
that their name and parentage should not be disgraced by the idea of defeat, but that they must expect victory and seize it as their right.

02:37.275 --> 02:42.000
No orator would have spoken to Spartans as to be oceans.

02:43.081 --> 02:49.949
It was their very life and business to fight, and deeds of prowess were therefore to be looked for from them.

02:51.130 --> 02:54.514
Is it not so with you, you followers of the crucified?

02:55.298 --> 03:02.509
Your martyrs and confesses call upon you to lead a life beyond that of the common men and women.

03:04.011 --> 03:12.945
I say all this because to certain of you, a sort of apology may seem needful for the strong things that may be said before you at this time.

03:14.066 --> 03:24.562
May God's Holy Spirit come upon you and make you strong enough for all the strong things, glorifying Himself in your weakness.

03:25.570 --> 03:29.655
Our first observation in plunging into our discourse is this.

03:30.837 --> 03:36.704
Much that is naturally good may fall far short of Christian character.

03:38.587 --> 03:42.451
Do not make the mistake of saying that moral excellence is not good.

03:43.653 --> 03:50.802
Some have broadly declared that there is no good thing in an unconverted man, but this is scarcely true.

03:51.746 --> 03:57.113
It will generally be so understood that its meaning will be false, and this is a great pity.

03:58.095 --> 04:01.720
We must not utter falsehood in order to honour God.

04:02.561 --> 04:04.343
There is a great deal of good.

04:05.365 --> 04:12.194
Good under certain senses and aspects of the term good in many unconverted people.

04:13.576 --> 04:21.106
Many who are total strangers to the grace of God yet exhibit sparkling forms of the human virtues

04:21.250 --> 04:28.360
in integrity, generosity, kindness, courage, self-sacrifice and patience.

04:29.621 --> 04:39.535
I could wish that some who call themselves Christians were in certain respects as good as others whom I know of, who have never borne the Christian name.

04:41.037 --> 04:47.125
It is always right to speak the truth, and truth obliges me to say as much as this.

04:48.207 --> 04:50.610
This ought to make professing Christians

04:50.690 --> 05:01.066
very seriously an earnest to judge themselves, lest they should mistake natural amiability and morality for the fruit of the Spirit of God.

05:02.548 --> 05:19.954
If the question be whether our character is the offspring of nature or of grace, it will be a sad thing if the verdict should turn out to be that it is the dead child of nature finally dressed, but not the living child of grace divine.

05:20.898 --> 05:31.093
we may be decorated with gems which glitter and glow, and yet they may be mere paste and none of them the work of God's Spirit.

05:32.435 --> 05:48.359
We may be adorned from head to foot with that which is lovely and of good repute, and for all that we may come short of what God requires of us because inwardly our heart is not in accordance with our outward array.

05:49.160 --> 05:50.642
The platter is clean,

05:51.330 --> 05:58.537
It could not be cleaner, but while the filth remains within, it cannot be acceptable with God.

06:00.018 --> 06:09.027
Observe the three things mentioned in the text against which there is no law, but of which much is to be spoken in commendation.

06:10.528 --> 06:15.793
These acts are good, but they do not come up to Christ's standard.

06:17.054 --> 06:20.978
The first is, if ye love them, which love you,

06:22.114 --> 06:28.083
It is very proper and seemingly that kindly feeling should awaken kindly feeling in return.

06:29.044 --> 06:32.970
That to those who are friendly to us, we should be friendly also.

06:34.032 --> 06:38.678
We say love begets love and it is natural that it should do so.

06:39.980 --> 06:49.234
Yet I am sorry to say that though this is no more than a natural excellence, it is not by any means so common as to be universal.

06:50.114 --> 07:03.088
There are children who do not love parents who toiled and slaved for them in their childhood, but who grow up to exhibit a strange hardness of heart to the authors of their existence.

07:04.249 --> 07:19.346
I know brothers who do not love the most affectionate and amiable of sisters, and it is grievous to have to add that there are many husbands who do not love their wives who are sacrificing their lives

07:19.586 --> 07:21.969
out of love to them and their little ones.

07:22.970 --> 07:30.478
I blush to think of the many instances which I could quote, but there is no need, you know it is so.

07:32.139 --> 07:35.803
Thousands have never reached so high as this standard.

07:36.965 --> 07:39.467
If you love them, which love you.

07:41.089 --> 07:46.415
But even if we reach as high as that, it is by no means a great attainment, is it?

07:47.536 --> 07:49.458
Our Lord says that sinners

07:49.634 --> 07:51.736
also love those that love them.

07:53.138 --> 07:57.663
Grace is not needed to make a man the loving husband of a tender wife.

07:58.784 --> 08:02.789
Grace is not needed to make affectionate sons and daughters.

08:03.650 --> 08:05.192
We see them all around us.

08:06.573 --> 08:15.504
I'm sure it does not require grace in the hearts of the bulk of you to make you feel kindly towards those who treat you in a friendly manner.

08:16.565 --> 08:17.586
Sinners also

08:17.954 --> 08:19.636
love those that love them.

08:19.676 --> 08:25.323
You have all come as far as that, and such feeling is good.

08:26.165 --> 08:27.346
The more of it, the better.

08:28.548 --> 08:33.754
Yet it is not up to the mark of Christ's teaching if it stands alone.

08:34.816 --> 08:38.360
It is not that for which the Holy Spirit has begotten us again.

08:38.400 --> 08:43.427
It is not that for which Christ has shed His precious blood.

08:44.368 --> 08:45.970
Higher virtue exists

08:46.146 --> 08:48.389
than that which loves those that love you.

08:49.270 --> 08:49.870
Here it is.

08:50.791 --> 08:55.377
We are to love them that hate us and, despitefully, entreat us.

08:56.598 --> 09:04.327
Can you love those who will not mention your name without grinding their teeth in envy or sneering in scorn?

09:05.348 --> 09:13.938
Can you love those who have belied your character, who have done the best they can to ruin you and will do the same again

09:15.202 --> 09:20.649
Can you feel towards them an earnest desire for their present and eternal welfare?

09:22.031 --> 09:25.856
If you could do them good, would you delight to do it?

09:26.677 --> 09:33.926
And repeat the deed until you made them too happy to be malicious, too indebted to continue at enmity.

09:35.087 --> 09:43.538
This would be glorious indeed, especially if you could keep clear of all selfish motive in such a contest of love.

09:44.482 --> 10:03.392
and should do it all not because you want to seem a hero or to be something great but simply because you delight to do good and feel it to be a pleasure to do that good where it is most needed, namely where the spirit of enmity has the greatest power.

10:05.195 --> 10:11.986
This is difficult and I think I hear someone say, I cannot attain unto it

10:12.866 --> 10:17.973
I can love those that love me, but loving those that hate me is another business.

10:19.235 --> 10:23.321
I shall have to look at the matter two or three times before I attempt it.

10:24.542 --> 10:33.595
I dare say you will, my friend, and hence it is that it needs the work of God Himself to make us Christians.

10:34.517 --> 10:41.266
It needs Father, Son, and Holy Spirit to work miracles of grace within us.

10:41.506 --> 10:43.148
air we become God-like.

10:44.549 --> 10:50.735
Godliness is God-likeness, and this is not easy to attain.

10:50.775 --> 10:57.701
The next thing in the verses before us is grateful return.

10:57.761 --> 11:03.467
If you do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye?

11:03.507 --> 11:10.994
It is a very right thing that if persons have served us, we should endeavour to repay the benefit.

11:11.714 --> 11:15.740
by common consent, one good turn deserves another.

11:17.242 --> 11:24.172
I am sorry to say that though this is a very ordinary sort of virtue, it is not the commonest thing in the world.

11:25.073 --> 11:30.802
For you may help others if you like, but I have heard that they do not always help you in return.

11:31.843 --> 11:39.474
I cannot speak from any painful experience here, for all have been kind to me, and I have had good measure

11:39.810 --> 11:44.154
pressed down and running over, poured into my heart.

11:45.355 --> 11:52.883
But I have met with men who have bitterly bewailed the ingratitude of those whom they had previously benefited.

11:53.844 --> 12:01.531
They claim to have helped others generously, but when their turn has come to need assistance, they have not received it.

12:03.073 --> 12:08.658
I do not feel very sure about the previous claim, but that is the way in which they talk.

12:09.730 --> 12:24.432
It is certainly a horrible thing that men should be ungrateful, but yet supposing that you, dear hearer, are grateful and have lately taken special pains to do good to one who a four-time was good to you.

12:24.492 --> 12:26.575
What thank have you?

12:26.635 --> 12:31.462
You have done what you ought to have done, and no more.

12:32.363 --> 12:36.850
You have paid an old debt, as every honest man should do.

12:37.826 --> 12:40.469
But this does not prove you to be a Christian.

12:41.411 --> 12:50.663
For Christianity includes this and rises above it, like an out above the surrounding plain.

12:50.683 --> 12:51.964
Thank you for listening, friends.

12:52.245 --> 12:57.031
This podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

12:57.632 --> 13:05.682
